						               													<description>Kingdom's Tarot: The Guardians of Destiny is a card game that allows the player to control one of the Lords of Tarot clans, these clans have similarity with the suits of the conventional deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal of each clan in that realm is to influence the maximum amount of souls possible, because it is the divine mission attributed to these clans. Of course, every soul has a different value. Each more valuable souls obtained, these lords will be send to the higher plane.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game can be played 2-4 players, each one will control a Lord of one of the clans, the clans have its own characteristics to play the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player uses a book that contains several cards that will change the game, with conditions, influence and destination cards. These cards will affect the souls of the board directly.&amp;#10;In the setup, before beginning of the first round, there will be a draft among the players to get the Majors Arcana Cards, these cards change instantly or permanently the conditions of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round 5 new souls will be revealed in &amp;quot;Souls Nursery&amp;quot; in this place players will be able to see who offers to influence souls when the soul is with an established influence it will incarnate.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On earth the soul will pass to three phases, past, present and future.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends after the first player intended seven souls, the one who gets the most soul points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
